# content-synced/ is written by `pnpm sync-content` and committed from the scripted sync.
# Keep the directory, ignore its contents here so an untouched scaffold has nothing to commit.
# When the sync script runs, it writes real files and the parent .gitignore does NOT ignore them;
# the sync workflow `git add -f content-synced/` then commits the snapshot explicitly.
*
!.gitignore
